\pard\keep\keepn\widctlpar\s1\sb240\sl252\slmult1\cf2\f2\fs32 Emulation limitations\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\cf0\f1\fs22 Emulation is mostly high-level with some low-level elements where it helps most. \par
Emulation of the Mega ST is partial. The Mega STE isn't emulated at all.\par
The light gun is not emulated (hard to do on an LCD screen!)\par
STE digital sound filters are not emulated. Microwire isn't accurate.\par
Only one mouse in port 0 is emulated.\par
The MC68901 MFP's "Pulse Width Measurement Operation" isn't emulated. Timer B emulation is pragmatic and a bit dodgy.\par
SCP: can't write disk images. Protections with weak bits can be trouble.\par
ACSI hard drive emulation is limited to the original Atari AHDI command set.\par
GEMDOS hard drive emulation is not guaranteed to be compatible with all programs (it's a hack after all).\par
\fs24 DMA transfer timing is approximate.\par
MIDI emulation doesn't support network games (MIDI Maze).\par
Drive seek sound isn't very good.\par
All the noise in sound and video output isn't emulated.\fs22\par
\par

\pard\keep\keepn\widctlpar\sb240\sl252\slmult1\cf2\f2\fs32\lang1033 Keyboard control\par

